Lake Flows: In the past 7 days 45,372 AF were discharged from Lake Okeechobee, with 20,186 AF (44%) to the Caloosahatchee through S-77, 3,049 AF (7%) to the St.Lucie River through S-308, 859 AF (2%) through S-310 in Clewiston, 4,631 AF (10%) through C-10A to the L-8 canal, and 16,647 AF (37%) to the EAA through S-351, S-352, and S-354. Water conservation areas received flows of 875 AF, 6,040 AF, and 0 AF at WCA1, WCA2, and WCA3,respectively. Everglades National Park received 3,638 AF.
